ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> talked</a> a few <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/29099936.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMTgvemlsbG93LXRyaWVkLXRvLW1ha2UtbGVzcy1t=
b25leT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTE5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3V=
yY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MTkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe5f8b4a9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> times</a> last year about Zillow =
Group Inc., which got into this business, and then got out of it in a hurry=
 after losing a bunch of money.=C2=A0There are two problems with the market=
 for homes, as opposed to the market for stocks:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It can take months to flip a house. Y=
ou buy it, maybe you spruce it up a bit, you re-list it, you do showings, e=
tc. So you have months of inventory risk rather than minutes.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can=E2=80=99t really short houses.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the market is rising, the market-maker mode=
l is very simple:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You bid the going=C2=A0price =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0maybe even a bit more than the going price =E2=80=94=C2=A0for hous=
es.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You buy a lot of them.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You spruce them up or whatever.</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You sell the houses a few months later, at =
the going price.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Meanwhile the pri=
ce has gone up so you make money.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
I suppose there is also a spread in here somewhere.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the market is falling, though, it=E2=80=99s=
 bad:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You bid the going price for houses. Y=
ou can=E2=80=99t bid=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>than the going price. Then you=
 wouldn=E2=80=99t get any houses, so you wouldn=E2=80=99t earn any spread, =
so the whole business wouldn=E2=80=99t work.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bot=
tom: 5px;">You buy a whole ton of houses, because in a falling market peopl=
e are going to be <em>more</em> likely to hit your bid. The more houses you=
 buy, the more you regret it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You =
spruce them up and sell a few months later at the going price.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Meanwhile the price has gone down so you lose =
money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, if you can correctly predict that the mar=
ket will go down, then the trade you will <em>want</em> to do is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You sell some houses at the going pri=
ce.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You wait a few months.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then you buy the houses back at the going=
 price and deliver them to your buyers.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">Meanwhile the price has gone down so you make money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But this trade does not work for houses. In th=
e stock market, you can provide immediacy to a buyer by borrowing stock and=
 selling it short. In the housing market, you can=E2=80=99t. People looking=
 to buy a house from you today will not want to wait months for you to buy =
it. It is fun to imagine workarounds =E2=80=94=C2=A0you rent the house and =
deliver it to the buyer, then you buy it later at a lower market price? =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0but they don=E2=80=99t really work either. (The buyer will want=
 title immediately, the seller won=E2=80=99t want to rent it to you, etc.) =
The market-maker-for-houses model involves a lot of long inventory risk tha=
t is hard to hedge.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29099936.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTkvaG9tZS1mbGlwcGVyLW9wZW5kb29yLWhpdC13aXRoLWxvc3Nlcy1pbi1=
lY2hvLW9mLXppbGxvdy1jb2xsYXBzZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTE5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbW=
VkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MTkmdXRtX2Nhb=
