Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Anyway</=
a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The [housing] slump has been especially harsh =
for Opendoor Technologies Inc., pioneer of a data-driven spin on home-flipp=
ing known as iBuying.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company, which sells thousands of homes in=
 a typical month, lost money on 42% of its transactions in August, accordin=
g to research from YipitData. Opendoor=E2=80=99s performance =E2=80=94 as m=
easured by the prices at which it bought and sold properties =E2=80=94 was =
even worse in key markets such as Los Angeles, where the company lost money=
 on 55% of sales, and Phoenix, where the share was 76%.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah if you are in the business of buying hous=
es and then selling them months later, and house prices go down, you will l=
ose money. This seems hard to avoid.</p>
