<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic idea of market manipulation is that =
you buy a lot of X to make the price of X go up, and then you own a lot of =
X, which is now worth more than you paid for it. If you start buying Stock =
X at $50, and you keep buying until you=E2=80=99ve pushed the price up to $=
100, then you=E2=80=99ve paid an average of, say, $75 per share, but now it=
=E2=80=99s worth $100 per share. Good job. But then you try to sell it, to =
realize that profit, and it starts going down. If it went up as you bought =
it, it should go down as you sell it. It=E2=80=99ll end up back at $50, may=
be lower. You won=E2=80=99t make any money on the trade.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a folk understanding of market manipu=
lation that it is=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0</em>this =E2=80=94=C2=A0just buying s=
tock to make it go up =E2=80=94=C2=A0and every so often you see someone acc=
used of this simple version. Bill Hwang of Archegos Capital Management is a=
 recent case that we=E2=80=99ve talked about a lot; he seems to have=C2=A0<=
em>lost=C2=A0</em>a fortune by buying tons of some stocks as they went. up,=
 and then selling them all at once in fire sales that crashed their prices.=
 He was arrested for manipulation anyway, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/29099936.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjcvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1hcnJlc3QtaW5zaWRlLX=
RoZS12aWNpb3VzLWN5Y2xlLW9mLWFyY2hlZ29zLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MTkyMl9NT=
05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJt=
PTIyMDkxOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB87c53ea=
5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  I have said</a>: huh?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, for market manipulation to make sense=
, you need a story that is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I can buy a lot of X and make it go u=
p,=C2=A0<em>and</em>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then I can sell it without making=
 it go down.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the general case this will not be true. If =
buying makes X go up, selling will make it go down, and so you can=E2=80=99=
t make money. There may be small exceptions; if you have a deep feel for ma=
rket dynamics, perhaps you can buy in ways that maximize price impact and s=
ell in ways that minimize it and thus make a round-trip profit. (There=E2=
=80=99s a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29099936=
.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDY=
tMjMvcmV2bG9uLWlzLWdldHRpbmctbWVtZWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkxOTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdX=
RtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTE5JnV0b=
V9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0510f80c" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  fu=
n niche theory</a> that in fact big hedge funds=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>routi=
nely manipulate stock prices by buying when liquidity is poor in the mornin=
g, which pushes up prices, and selling when liquidity is good in the aftern=
oon, which does not push them back down.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But for the most part, the way market manipula=
tion works is that you have some sort of price-insensitive buyer lined up t=
o sell to before you start buying to manipulate the price. Often this invol=
ves some sort of derivative that settles by reference to the market price, =
which you then manipulate. If you have a contract saying that you can sell =
100,000 units to your counterparty at the market price as of 4 p.m., you mi=
ght consider buying=C2=A0100,000 units, as noisily as possible, between 3:5=
8 and 3:59. You=E2=80=99ll push up the price a lot with your buying, and th=
en you can just dump it on your price-insensitive counterparty at 4 p.m. Th=
is is a classic =E2=80=94=C2=A0there was a string of <a href=3D"https://lin=
