"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> it says</a>. Ordinarily th=
e way financial markets work is that trades have =E2=80=9Cslippage,=E2=80=
=9D or =E2=80=9Cprice impact=E2=80=9D: If you buy a little, the price will =
go up a little; if you buy a lot, it will go up a lot; if you sell, it will=
 go down.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People find this strangely offensive =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0a lot of arguments over high-frequency trading in the stock market or=
 liquidity in the bond market come down to =E2=80=9CI want to be able to bu=
y and sell financial assets without moving their price=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0and GMX came up with =E2=80=A6=C2=A0a =E2=80=A6=C2=A0solution? The so=
lution is that GMX just looks at the market price of a token on some other =
exchange, and then sells you as much as you want of that token (in the form=
 of a perpetual swap) at the market price: =E2=80=9CThere is <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29099936.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly9nbXhp=
by5naXRib29rLmlvL2dteC90cmFkaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf83cffeb" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
> no price impact</a> for trades on GMX, so you can execute large trades ex=
actly at the mark price.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0(This is called =E2=80=9Coracle=E2=
=80=9D pricing: GMX=E2=80=99s price comes from looking at the price on othe=
r exchanges, rather than from supply and demand on GMX itself.)=C2=A0If the=
 Avalanche blockchain=E2=80=99s AVAX token is trading at $17 on some exchan=
ge, and you want to buy swaps on=C2=A0100,000 AVAX tokens on GMX, you=E2=80=
=99ll pay $17.00 per token. If you went to some other exchange to actually =
buy 100,000 AVAX tokens, there would be price impact, and you might end up =
paying $17.50 or whatever. But on GMX, there is no slippage, and you pay $1=
7.00.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You probably know where this is going? I proba=
bly don=E2=80=99t need to write the rest of it? I have that experience a lo=
t, writing about crypto. Often it feels like I could=C2=A0just describe the=
 mechanics of how a thing works, and then leave it as an exercise for the r=
eader to explain how it was exploited. This one is very easy. Maybe stop re=
ading for a second, figure out your answer, and then go on to the next para=
graph.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So sure yeah <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/29099936.278538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL21=
hcmtldHMvMjAyMi8wOS8xOS9kZWZpLXRyYWRlci1uZXRzLW92ZXItNTAway1ieS11c2luZy1kZX=
