<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This isn't an exploit as much as GMX working a=
s designed! [The trader]=C2=A0executed large trades in against [GMX=E2=80=
=99s decentralized liquidity providers]=C2=A0with 0 slippage: at the oracle=
 price without factoring any price impact</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the real world, putting on risk requires yo=
u to pay liquidity providers on the opposite side.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes if you can trade a thing in large size wit=
hout moving its price, and you can also (on a regular exchange) trade the t=
hing in large size <em>with=C2=A0</em>moving its price, then you can print =
free money, and someone did.</p>
